{{unreferenced|date=September 2015}}
'''Jalisco Philharmonic Orchestra''' (Orquesta Filarmónica de Jalisco) was established in 1912 by José Rolón as the Guadalajara Symphonic Orchestra in [[Guadalajara]], [[Jalisco]] in [[Mexico]]. The Orchestra resides at [[Teatro Degollado]] located in the historic district of Guadalajara.

It has been conducted by [[Enrique Bátiz]], [[Neeme Järvi]]{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}, [[Plácido Domingo]]{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}, [[Mu-Hai Tang]], [[Claudio Abbado]]{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}, [[Antal Doráti]]{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}, [[Eduardo Mata]] and [[Charles Dutoit]]{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}. [[Alondra de la Parra]] was the artistic director from 2012 to 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://eleconomista.com.mx/entretenimiento/2012/03/30/alondra-parra-dirigira-orquesta-filarmonica-jalisco|title=Alondra de la Parra dirigirá la Orquesta Filarmónica de Jalisco|work=[[El Economista (Mexico)|El Economista]]|author= |date=2012-03-30|accessdate=2015-11-28|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.unionjalisco.mx/articulo/2013/01/24/musica/florence-cassez-y-alondra-de-la-parra-el-fin-de-dos-historias|title=Florence Cassez y Alondra de la Parra: el fin de dos historias|work=Union Jalisco|author= |date=2013-01-24|accessdate=2015-11-28|language=es}}</ref>

